To use the new configure script to install MaGe please install
ROOT, PGSQL, and GEANT4 according to their instruction sets.

Then, in the base directory of MaGe run ./configure
This will try to find the dependencies of MaGe.  Please
follow any instructions the configure script gives if an error
occurs.  Once configure has completed successfully, run

make 

This should compile and install MaGe.

Common options to configure:

  --disable-database      Disable database. Database is enabled by default.  
  --enable-no-skip        Doesn't skip any of the packages (e.g. waveform)

For the full list of flags and options for configure, do

configure --help
